<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<package>
  <metadata>
    <id>bbv.Common.DistributedEventBroker</id>
    <version>%bbv.Common.DistributedEventBrokerFileVersion%</version>
    <projectUrl>http://code.google.com/p/bbvcommon/</projectUrl>
    <authors>bbv Software Services AG and Contributers</authors>
    <iconUrl>https://github.com/bbvcommon/bbv.Common/raw/master/documents/nuget.png</iconUrl>
    <summary>Extension for the bbv.Common.EventBroker to allow distribution of events over processes.</summary>
    <description>With this extension, the event broker can be used to fire events to event brokers in remote processes.

      bbv.Common.DistributedEventBroker is a part of bbv.Common, a library of .NET components and functionality including:
      * (a)synchronous notification component with thread switching using publisher-subscriber pattern,
      * hierarchical state machine with fluent definition syntax,
      * programmatic, loosely coupled, context based rule engine,
      * support for active objects to build multi-threaded applications</description>
    <tags>event-broker extension interprocess-communication distributed</tags>
    <language>en-US</language>
